fields.history_note: Printed sheet of rules, and cards and counters all contained in original wood box with sliding lid bearing a hand coloured lithograph.
fields.historical_context_note:
Rewards: according to the directions - rewards from the pool and other players
Forfeits: according to the directions - forfeits to the pool and other players
No. of Players: any
Equipment required: 30 card with illustrations of characters with lettered titles; each is numbered with a number between 1 and 6
30 cards, green, printed with instructions, rhymes etc, also numbered between 1 and 6
40 rectangular counters with printed design

Rules:
TOBY TOTT AND CHRISTMAS PUDDING A NEW COMIC GAME WITH CARDS
FUN AND LAUGHTER FOR CHRISTMAS AND AFTER

DIRECTIONS TO PLAY.
Mix the Cards well and divide them equally among the players, if any odd Cards remain put them aside, also, divide the counters.  Each must then give two counters to form a Pool.
The oldest among the players should begin the game by turning over the uppermost card he holds, his right hand neighbour doing the same with his uppermost card, the player of the card with the highest number to take the two cards.
The second player must repeat this process with the third player, the third with the fourth and the last player will turn over his card to the player who began the game and so on till all the cards  given out are distributed.
The players then are to gather up their cards, each party keeping his own, well mix them, pack them and play them as at first.
When the player having most of the following cards wins the game, THE PUDDING, TOBY TOTT, CURRANTS, BRANDY, MILK, SUGAR, EGGS, CANDIED PEEL, FLOUR SPICE.  When two cards are alike in number they must be thrown aside.
The forfeits to the Pool and each other must be strictly paid.
If a riddle cannot be answered it may be passed over.
Any other ingredient used in making a Pudding may be named by a player at the end of the game who on looking over his cards can be the first to pick out  a card numbered 2 thus SUET etc.
This card must be held aloft and the ingredient mentioned giving the player one additional to his score.
